upstream: https://github.com/akinomyoga/ble.sh
commit:   b99cadb4520a1fdec0067fdc007b39cc905ecbad
date:     2026-03-11
built:    make (from commit above, with contrib/ submodule empty — opt-in plugins not needed)
audit:    docs/decisions.md D016 — ble.sh+bash-preexec+carapace security audits (2026-04-11)

Contents are the build output of `make` from the pinned upstream source tree.
The source tree was audited (single-maintainer Koichi Murase, ~900 internal evals
all over pre-parsed literals/state arrays, temp files under umask 077 with TOCTOU
guards, no runtime network, clean CI). No contrib/ plugins included.

Upgrade workflow (matches D013 vendor flow):
  1. git clone https://github.com/akinomyoga/ble.sh /tmp/blesh && cd /tmp/blesh
  2. git checkout <new-commit>
  3. re-run the audit agent
  4. make
  5. rm -rf /opt/arche/vendor/blesh/* && cp -a out/. /opt/arche/vendor/blesh/
  6. cp LICENSE.md /opt/arche/vendor/blesh/
  7. update this .source with new commit hash + date

Do NOT call `ble-update` inside the shell — upgrades happen by re-vendoring only.
